<p>The <code>lower</code> function converts text to lowercase.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'HELLO WORLD' | lower{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{'HELLO WORLD' | lower}</b></p>

<h2>Normalize Input</h2>
<pre>{open}'JoHn.DoE@EXAMPLE.COM' | lower{close}</pre>
<p>Email normalized: <b>{'JoHn.DoE@EXAMPLE.COM' | lower}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}'FILE.TXT' | lower | before('.'){close}</pre>
<p>Lowercase filename without extension: <b>{'FILE.TXT' | lower | before('.')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'  HELLO WORLD  ' | trim | lower | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Clean and title case: <b>{'  HELLO WORLD  ' | trim | lower | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>URL Slugs</h2>
<pre>{open}'My Blog Post Title' | lower | replace(' ', '-'){close}</pre>
<p>URL slug: <b>{'My Blog Post Title' | lower | replace(' ', '-')}</b></p>

<h2>Complex Chain</h2>
<pre>{open}'USER: JOHN_DOE' | after(': ') | lower | replace('_', ' ') | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Format username: <b>{'USER: JOHN_DOE' | after(': ') | lower | replace('_', ' ') | capitalize}</b></p>
